// Typecheck the TESTS.
//
// The main tsconfig excludes **/*.test.ts, because Next.js should not compile
// them into the app. The side effect was that the test files were the one part
// of the codebase the compiler never looked at — and vitest does not typecheck
// either, it just runs. So a test could go on referring to a field that no
// longer exists, quietly asserting things about `undefined`.
//
// That is not hypothetical: renaming `price` → `priceMinor` left view.test.ts
// still building items with a `price`, and `npm run typecheck` said everything
// was fine. A test that cannot fail to compile is a test you cannot trust.
//
// `npm run typecheck:tests` covers them. Run it with the other checks.
{
  "extends": "./tsconfig.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "noEmit": true
  },
  "include": ["src/**/*.ts", "src/**/*.tsx"],
  "exclude": ["node_modules"]
}
